title: Activation cross sections of proton induced nuclear reactions on ytterbium up to 70 MeV

x4freetext: Activation cross sections of proton induced nuclear
reactions on ytterbium up to 70 MeV

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.267, p.2789 (2009)

x4freetext: Yb target foils, thickness: 23 micron
Three irradiations were performed.
The activity of the irradiated samples was measured
nondestructively, without chemical separation.
VUB: the samples were measured three times; two
measurements were performed shortly after end of
bombardment and the third one was done about one month
later.
CYRIC: the samples were measured three times as well,
but the first measurements started about 24 h after
end of bombardment due to the high dose rate of the
irradiated stack.
The effect of the secondary neutrons was checked by
placing extra target foils at the end of the stack
exposed only to possible secondary neutrons. Recoil
losses were estimated from recoil contamination of the
adjacent Al monitor foils. Both effects were
negligible in these experiments.
16 MeV proton beam, 190 nA, 1 h, Belgium (VUB)
36 MeV proton beam, 140 nA, 1 h, Belgium (VUB)
70 MeV proton beam, 130 nA, 0.5 h, Japan (CYRIC)
Al foils, thickness: 100-200 micron and
Ti foils, thickness: 12 micron
Chapter 4

x4freetext: Volume 3
The mean proton energies in the successive target
foils were determined by calculation from the
bombarding energies, stack compositions and foil
thicknesses.
Decay data were taken from NuDat database.
Not specified.
The uncertainties were estimated in the
standard way: the independent relative uncertainties
were quadratically summed and its square root was
taken.
number of target nuclei
uniformity of the samples
detector efficiency
peak area analysis
beam current
decay data (gamma intensity)
counting statistics: 0.1-30%
The experimental data were compared to and
analyzed with the results of the theoretical model
code ALICE-IPPE (in addition EMPIRE and TALYS in case
of 175Yb).
On the basis of the experimental data and the
results of the ALICE-IPPE model code integral yields
for production of the investigated reaction products
were calculated.
